♪ I can make it ♪

67
00:02:16,178 --> 00:02:18,555
♪ Whatever it takes ♪

68
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:20,766
♪ I know I can make it through ♪

69
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:23,769
ELI:
CLARE! CLARE!

70
00:02:24,645 --> 00:02:25,562
(PANTING)

71
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:27,105
OKAY, I CAN'T TELL...

72
00:02:27,189 --> 00:02:28,982
ARE YOU EXCITED
OR ARE YOU FREAKING OUT?

73
00:02:29,066 --> 00:02:30,776
BOTH.

74
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:32,736
THIS IS GONNA BE
THE BEST TERM EVER!

75
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:35,489
OKAY...
UM, I'LL BITE. WHY?

76
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:36,490
BRET BARNETT WILL BE
GUEST LECTURING

77
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:39,409
IN OUR CLASS THIS WEEK.

78
00:02:39,493 --> 00:02:41,286
THE BRET BARNETT?

79
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:42,829
THE CRITICALLY
AND COMMERCIALLY

80
00:02:42,913 --> 00:02:44,081
ACCLAIMED DIRECTOR
BRET BARNETT;

81
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:46,708
THE SUNDANCE AWARD-WINNING
BRET BARNETT;

82
00:02:46,792 --> 00:02:50,128
AND MOST IMPORTANTLY,
THE NYU GRAD, BRET BARNETT.

83
00:02:50,212 --> 00:02:51,421
SO YOU CAN GET HIM
TO...

84
00:02:51,505 --> 00:02:52,130
BOTH:
WRITE ME-YOU A REFERENCE LETTER
FOR NYU.

85
00:02:52,214 --> 00:02:53,799
PRECISELY.

86
00:02:53,882 --> 00:02:54,383
I'LL SHOW OFF
MY FILMMAKING KNOWLEDGE,

87
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:56,468
HE'LL BE IMPRESSED,

88
00:02:56,552 --> 00:02:57,761
AND HE'LL WRITE
A GLOWING RECOMMENDATION!

89
00:02:57,845 --> 00:03:00,222
(BOTH GIGGLE)

90
00:03:00,305 --> 00:03:01,515
MARISOL:
GOOD MORNING, DEGRASSI!

91
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:03,100
PREPARATION IS UNDER WAY

92
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:05,519
FOR THE DEGRASSI
FUNDRAISER GALA.

93
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:07,563
OUR GOAL IS TO RAISE $12,000
FOR THE SCHOOL...

94
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:10,107
FIONA:
TELL. ME. EVERYTHING!

95
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:10,983
BIANCA:
YOU'RE GONNA NEED
TO BE MORE SPECIFIC.

96
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:12,776
THE ENGAGEMENT?

97
00:03:12,860 --> 00:03:14,987
DID HE GET DOWN ON ONE KNEE?
DETAILS, GIRL!

98
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:17,406
IT WAS SIMPLE.
SWEET.

99
00:03:17,489 --> 00:03:18,866
I DUNNO.
OH, YOU'RE NO FUN.

100
00:03:18,949 --> 00:03:20,534
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

101
00:03:20,617 --> 00:03:22,119
WHERE'S YOUR RING?
I WANNA SEE.

102
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:31,712
OH! IT'S...CUTE.

103
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:32,921
AND HIDDEN FOR A REASON.

104
00:03:33,005 --> 00:03:34,214
SO WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

105
00:03:34,298 --> 00:03:36,508
WE HAVEN'T TOLD AUDRA.

106
00:03:36,592 --> 00:03:37,926
DREW'S CONVINCED
SHE'LL TALK US OUT OF IT.

107
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:39,219
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

108
00:03:39,303 --> 00:03:41,263
I DON'T KNOW.

109
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:41,847
I MEAN, DREW MIGHT NOT HAVE
A RELATIONSHIP WITH HIS MOM,

110
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:44,141
BUT I DO.

111
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,517
AND IF WE GET MARRIED
WITHOUT TELLING HER,

112
00:03:45,601 --> 00:03:47,644
IT COULD WRECK THAT.

113
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:49,771
WHEN IT COMES
TO SIGNIFICANT OTHERS' MOTHERS,

114
00:03:49,855 --> 00:03:53,358
SOMETIMES IT'S BEST TO LEAVE
WELL ENOUGH ALONE.

115
00:03:53,442 --> 00:03:54,735
YEAH,
YOU'RE RIGHT.

116
00:03:54,818 --> 00:03:56,069
LOOK AT YOU,
COMPROMISING.

117
00:03:56,153 --> 00:03:57,154
IT'S LIKE YOU'RE MARRIED
ALREADY.

118
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:58,739
YEAH.

119
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:01,241
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

120
00:04:03,744 --> 00:04:06,288
BECKY:
ADAM! HEY!

121
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:09,499
SO HOMEOSTASIS -
PRETTY COOL STUFF, HUH?

122
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:11,502
YEAH. RIGHT UP THERE
WITH WATCHING PAINT DRY.

123
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:12,920
BECKY:
I, UH...

124
00:04:13,003 --> 00:04:14,505
I WANTED TO ASK YOU
UM...

125
00:04:17,508 --> 00:04:19,009
WHAT?

126
00:04:20,177 --> 00:04:21,303
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO VOLUNTEER

127
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:23,430
FOR THE STUDENT COUNCIL
FUNDRAISER?

128
00:04:23,514 --> 00:04:25,390
OH.

129
00:04:25,474 --> 00:04:27,559
YOU KNOW, I'M PRETTY BUSY
WITH WHISPERHUG.

130
00:04:27,643 --> 00:04:28,936
NOW THAT THE MUSICAL'S OVER,

131
00:04:29,019 --> 00:04:30,312
WE'VE GOT SO MUCH WORK
TO DO.

132
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:32,814
IT'S FOR A GOOD CAUSE!

133
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:35,025
TO BE HONEST,

134
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:37,861
I'M NOT SURE US WORKING TOGETHER
IS THE GREATEST IDEA.

135
00:04:37,945 --> 00:04:39,863
(LOUD ROCK MUSIC PLAYS
THOUGH HEADPHONES)

136
00:04:39,947 --> 00:04:40,489
MO: (YELLING)
IMOGEN IS GETTING THE KEY
FOR THE DOOR

137
00:04:40,572 --> 00:04:41,532
'CAUSE IT'S LOCKED!

138
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:44,409
CAN'T GET IN WITHOUT A KEY.

139
00:04:44,493 --> 00:04:46,537
I KNOW WE GOT OFF
TO A SHAKY START,

140
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:47,538
BUT WHEN YOU LET ME SING
IN THE MUSICAL,

141
00:04:47,621 --> 00:04:49,122
IT REALLY OPENED MY MIND.

142
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:52,835
ADAM:
MO? MO!

143
00:04:52,918 --> 00:04:54,586
CAN YOU EXPLAIN TO BECKY

144
00:04:54,670 --> 00:04:55,921
THAT I CAN'T HELP
WITH THE FUNDRAISER

145
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:57,422
BECAUSE WE'VE GOT BAND PRACTICE
ALL WEEK?

146
00:04:57,506 --> 00:04:59,007
MY MAN DOESN'T LIE.

147
00:05:00,926 --> 00:05:01,927
NINER, DO YOU MIND
IF I BORROW ADAM?

148
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:03,595
IT'S FOR STUDENT COUNCIL.

149
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:05,097
UH, I DON'T KNOW.

150
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:05,639
DON'T WE HAVE
A BATTLE OF THE BANDS

151
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:07,558
COMING UP SOON?

152
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,017
SO YOU NEED PRACTICE

153
00:05:09,101 --> 00:05:10,644
PLAYING IN FRONT
OF A LIVE AUDIENCE?

154
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:12,855
I GUESS SO.

155
00:05:12,938 --> 00:05:14,523
WHY DOESN'T WHISPERHUG PERFORM
AT THE FUNDRAISER?

156
00:05:14,606 --> 00:05:16,108
MO:
OOH! GAME-CHANGER.

157
00:05:18,652 --> 00:05:20,153
DON'T MAKE ME
REGRET THIS.

158
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:24,241
TOWNSEND:
LADIES AND GERMS,

159
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,660
AS PROMISED,
OUR GUEST FOR THE WEEK,

160
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:28,495
RENOWNED DIRECTOR
BRET BARNETT.

161
00:05:28,579 --> 00:05:30,497
(APPLAUSE)

162
00:05:30,581 --> 00:05:32,374
NOW, UNDER HIS TUTELAGE,

163
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:34,793
EACH ONE OF YOU WILL PRODUCE
A SHORT FILM.

164
00:05:34,877 --> 00:05:36,587
BRET:
TWO MINUTES,
ANY TOPIC.

165
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:38,547
THEN WE'LL DO CRITIQUES.

166
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:40,132
YOU GOT QUESTIONS?

167
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:43,135
YEAH.

168
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:44,469
UM, I NOTICED
IN MANNY'S ISLAND

169
00:05:44,553 --> 00:05:46,388
THAT YOU BROKE THE AXIS
A FEW TIMES.

170
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:48,849
UH, IS THAT SOMETHING
THAT YOU'D ENCOURAGE?

171
00:05:48,932 --> 00:05:50,058
WELL, IF I DID BREAK THE AXIS,
IT WASN'T ON PURPOSE.

172
00:05:50,142 --> 00:05:51,643
BUT THANKS FOR THAT.

173
00:05:54,146 --> 00:05:56,148
UH, YOUR FREQUENT USE
OF AMBIENT LIGHT...

174
00:05:56,231 --> 00:05:57,858
IS THAT SOMETHING
YOU'D RECOMMEND FOR OUR FILMS?

175
00:05:57,941 --> 00:05:59,735
UNLESS YOU GOT
THOUSANDS OF DOLLARS

176
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:00,319
TO SHELL OUT FOR A PROFESSIONAL
LIGHTING PACKAGE,

177
00:06:00,402 --> 00:06:01,904
THEN YEAH.

178
00:06:04,031 --> 00:06:05,407
AND FINALLY, WHAT'S YOUR STANCE
ON FILM VERSUS DIGITAL?

179
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,034
DIGITAL'S CHEAPER,

180
00:06:07,117 --> 00:06:08,327
BUT FILM HAS
AN ATMOSPHERIC QUALITY-

181
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:10,412
YEAH, NO, LOOK...

182
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:14,291
NONE OF THIS TECH STUFF MATTERS
UNLESS YOU GOT A GOOD STORY.

183
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:15,209
WELL, HOW DO YOU KNOW
IF YOU HAVE A GOOD STORY?

184
00:06:15,292 --> 00:06:17,419
OKAY, WELL...

185
00:06:17,503 --> 00:06:19,213
UH, GREAT ARTISTS,

186
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:23,467
THEY USE THEIR MEDIUM
TO SAY SOMETHING.

187
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:25,427
SO I DON'T KNOW...
YOU WANNA IMPRESS ME?

188
00:06:25,511 --> 00:06:27,012
DO THAT.

189
00:06:30,182 --> 00:06:32,017
FIONA:
AND FINALLY,
WE'LL GET THE UPDATES

190
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,602
FROM ALL OF OUR HEAD VOLUNTEERS

191
00:06:33,685 --> 00:06:34,937
FOR THE BIG STUDENT COUNCIL
FUNDRAISER.

192
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:37,064
SO DECORATIONS?

193
00:06:37,147 --> 00:06:38,690
TOTALLY UNDER CONTROL.

194
00:06:38,774 --> 00:06:40,943
FIONA:
OKAY. AND REFRESHMENTS?

195
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:42,152
I FOUND A CATERER
WHO'LL DO IT FOR FREE.

196
00:06:42,236 --> 00:06:43,278
AWESOME.

197
00:06:43,362 --> 00:06:45,280
AND DONATIONS?

198
00:06:45,364 --> 00:06:46,198
HELLO? DONATIONS?

199
00:06:46,281 --> 00:06:47,574
UH, BECKY BAKER,

200
00:06:47,658 --> 00:06:50,035
HEAD OF SILENT AUCTION
DONATIONS.

201
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:52,496
I HAVE REALLY BIG NEWS:
ADAM HAS JOINED MY TEAM.

202
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:56,583
THAT'S IT?

203
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,460
JENNA:
AND BECKY SCORED US SEVEN
PLANE TICKETS TO VEGAS

204
00:06:58,544 --> 00:06:59,670
TO AUCTION OFF.

205
00:06:59,753 --> 00:07:01,171
FIONA:
THAT'S AMAZING!

206
00:07:01,255 --> 00:07:03,340
EVEN MORE AMAZING,
ADAM'S BAND, WHISPERHUG,

207
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:04,675
IS GOING TO BE PLAYING
DURING THE EVENT!

208
00:07:04,758 --> 00:07:06,260
(APPLAUDS)

209
00:07:08,929 --> 00:07:12,933
OKAY, LET'S BREAK UP INTO GROUPS
AND GET TO WORK!

210
00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:14,309
ADAM:
I'M ON THE DONATIONS COMMITTEE?

211
00:07:14,393 --> 00:07:15,686
WHAT DO WE DO,
EXACTLY?

212
00:07:15,769 --> 00:07:17,020
WELL, WE'RE GOING TO GO
DOOR-TO-DOOR

213
00:07:17,104 --> 00:07:18,647
TO LOCAL BUSINESSES

214
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,691
TO SEE IF THEY'LL DONATE ITEMS
FOR THE AUCTION,

215
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:21,567
AND WE'LL HIT THE MALL
AFTER SCHOOL!

216
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:22,568
LUKE:
WEARING THESE.

217
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:24,152
(GIGGLES)

218
00:07:26,363 --> 00:07:27,489
JENNA:
SO WHAT'S YOUR STRATEGY HERE?

219
00:07:27,573 --> 00:07:28,824
DID YOU ASK HIM OUT?

220
00:07:28,907 --> 00:07:30,242
I CHICKENED OUT

221
00:07:30,325 --> 00:07:31,285
AND ASKED HIM TO DO
THIS INSTEAD.

222
00:07:31,368 --> 00:07:33,161
REJECTION'S TOUGH,

223
00:07:33,245 --> 00:07:36,665
BUT IT'S BETTER TO KNOW
IF THE GUY DOESN'T LIKE YOU.

224
00:07:36,748 --> 00:07:38,667
BECKY:
YOU'RE RIGHT;
I HAVE TO FIND OUT.

225
00:07:46,216 --> 00:07:47,968
BIG MALL ADVENTURE TONIGHT!

226
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:53,557
I WORRY MAYBE
I FORCED YOU TO WORK

227
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,309
ON THE SILENT AUCTION.

228
00:07:55,392 --> 00:07:56,560
YA THINK?

229
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:59,062
WELL, YOU DON'T HAVE TO,

230
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:00,522
AND YOUR BAND CAN STILL PLAY
NO MATTER WHAT.

231
00:08:00,606 --> 00:08:01,982
BUT I HOPE YOU WANT TO,

232
00:08:02,065 --> 00:08:03,317
'CAUSE WORKING ON THE EVENT

233
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,902
MEANS YOU'D HELP
THE SCHOOL,

234
00:08:04,985 --> 00:08:07,321
AND YOU'D GET TO WORK CLOSELY
WITH PEOPLE LIKE...

235
00:08:07,404 --> 00:08:08,906
LIKE JENNA?

236
00:08:11,241 --> 00:08:13,911
YES.

237
00:08:13,994 --> 00:08:16,830
AND FIONA, AND MARISOL,
AND LUKE, AND...

238
00:08:16,914 --> 00:08:18,415
YOU?

239
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:20,667
BUT ONLY IF YOU WANT TO...

240
00:08:20,751 --> 00:08:22,252
WHICH I HOPE YOU DO,

241
00:08:22,336 --> 00:08:26,798
BECAUSE I'D LIKE TO WORK
CLOSELY WITH YOU.

242
00:08:26,882 --> 00:08:28,550
WE ARE HELPING THE SCHOOL
RAISE MONEY.

243
00:08:30,052 --> 00:08:31,553
IS THAT A YES?

244
00:08:32,804 --> 00:08:34,473
I'LL SEE YOU AT THE MALL
TONIGHT.

245
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:43,440
BIANCA:
IS IT GOOD ENOUGH TO WIN ME
FIVE GRAND IN SCHOLARSHIP MONEY?

246
00:08:43,524 --> 00:08:46,610
BIANCA,
THIS IS BEAUTIFUL.

247
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:49,530
WOW, I WISH DREW HAD
YOUR DETERMINATION.

248
00:08:49,613 --> 00:08:51,114
DREW DOES.

249
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:51,698
HE'S DOING REALLY GREAT
AT HIS JOB.

250
00:08:51,782 --> 00:08:54,493
YOU SHOULD SEE HIM.

251
00:08:54,576 --> 00:08:56,787
HAS HE MADE ANY LIFE-ALTERING
DECISIONS THIS WEEK?

252
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,372
NO. WHY?

253
00:09:00,582 --> 00:09:02,835
WELL, YOU KNOW,
HE DROPPED OUT OF SCHOOL,

254
00:09:02,918 --> 00:09:04,545
BOUGHT A MOTORCYCLE...

255
00:09:04,628 --> 00:09:07,214
WHAT'S NEXT?

256
00:09:07,297 --> 00:09:08,507
FOR ALL I KNOW,
HE'S GONNA MOVE TO JAPAN.

257
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:10,092
NO. NOTHING NEW.

258
00:09:11,552 --> 00:09:13,053
(SIGHS HEAVILY)
I JUST FEEL SO...

259
00:09:14,847 --> 00:09:16,348
OUT OF TOUCH
WITH HIS LIFE.

260
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:20,269
BUT AT LEAST I KNOW
HE HAS YOU.

261
00:09:20,352 --> 00:09:22,312
YEAH. HE DOES.

262
00:09:22,396 --> 00:09:24,356
HE DEFINITELY DOES.

263
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,608
GOOD.

264
00:09:26,692 --> 00:09:30,571
♪♪♪

265
00:09:30,654 --> 00:09:31,989
♪ Try to forget you ♪

266
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:34,449
♪ But every other day
I'm callin' ♪

267
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:36,577
♪ Said I take you up ♪

268
00:09:36,660 --> 00:09:38,287
♪ But every time
you're always stalling ♪

269
00:09:38,370 --> 00:09:40,080
♪ You got a friend ♪

270
00:09:40,163 --> 00:09:42,374
♪ Until your goldfish
needs a surgery ♪

271
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:44,251
♪ You said your car exploded ♪

272
00:09:44,334 --> 00:09:46,044
♪ Don't be a heartbreaker! ♪

273
00:09:46,128 --> 00:09:48,255
♪ Hey boy! ♪

274
00:09:48,338 --> 00:09:50,048
♪ I know you don't know me ♪

275
00:09:50,132 --> 00:09:52,009
♪ I'm right where you want me ♪

276
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:53,969
♪ I could be perfect for you ♪

277
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:55,929
♪ My world ♪

278
00:09:56,013 --> 00:09:57,764
♪ You put the moves on me ♪

279
00:09:57,848 --> 00:09:59,850
♪ And it was so easy ♪

280
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:01,685
♪ Why can't I talk to you ♪

281
00:10:01,768 --> 00:10:03,729
♪ Hey boy ♪

282
00:10:03,812 --> 00:10:05,647
♪ I need your money ♪

283
00:10:05,731 --> 00:10:07,649
♪ I feel so good ♪
(so good)

284
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:09,568
♪ You're on my mind ♪

285
00:10:09,651 --> 00:10:11,570
♪ Hey boy ♪

286
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:13,447
♪ I know you don't know me ♪

287
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:15,240
♪ I feel so good ♪

288
00:10:15,324 --> 00:10:16,408
BECKY:
IF YOU GIVE US MERCHANDISE,

289
00:10:16,491 --> 00:10:18,368
WE'LL MAKE SURE
YOUR BRANDING IS VISIBLE.

290
00:10:18,452 --> 00:10:20,162
ADAM:
LOGOS THE SIZE OF YOUR HEAD.

291
00:10:20,245 --> 00:10:21,914
OKAY, I'LL GET YOU
SOME HOODIES.

292
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:26,543
ADAM:
WHILE WE WAIT,

293
00:10:26,627 --> 00:10:27,252
I'M GONNA GO TRY ON THAT SWEATER
OVER THERE, OKAY?

294
00:10:27,336 --> 00:10:28,837
OKAY.

295
00:10:32,674 --> 00:10:34,468
I THINK THAT ADAM PERSON
LIKES YOU.

296
00:10:34,551 --> 00:10:36,261
REALLY?
YOU THINK SO?

297
00:10:36,345 --> 00:10:39,223
'CAUSE I WAS HOPING,
BUT I WASN'T SURE.

298
00:10:39,306 --> 00:10:41,266
LUKE:
OKAY. WHATEVER'S GOING ON HERE,
END IT.

299
00:10:41,350 --> 00:10:42,768
GIVE ME ONE GOOD REASON.

300
00:10:42,851 --> 00:10:44,019
I'LL GIVE YOU TWO:
MOM AND DAD.

301
00:10:44,102 --> 00:10:46,063
HOW DO YOU THINK
THEY'D FEEL ABOUT IT?

302
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:47,689
YOU CAN'T SAY ANYTHING!

303
00:10:47,773 --> 00:10:48,857
BUT I KNOW YOU,
BECKS.

304
00:10:48,941 --> 00:10:50,192
ARE YOU REALLY GOING
TO BE HAPPY

305
00:10:50,275 --> 00:10:52,653
DATING SOMEONE THAT MOM AND DAD
WILL NEVER APPROVE OF?

306
00:10:52,736 --> 00:10:54,613
♪ Hey boy ♪

307
00:10:54,696 --> 00:10:57,032
♪ I know you don't know me ♪

308
00:10:57,115 --> 00:10:59,993
♪ I'm right where you want me,
I could be perfect... ♪

309
00:11:05,707 --> 00:11:08,544
I DON'T HAVE A SINGLE GOOD IDEA
FOR THIS SHORT FILM.

310
00:11:08,627 --> 00:11:10,128
CAN YOU HELP ME?
YEAH.

311
00:11:11,046 --> 00:11:13,882
UH, CONFLICT
IN THE MIDDLE EAST?

312
00:11:13,966 --> 00:11:16,051
THE DECLINE OF
WESTERN CIVILIZATION?

313
00:11:16,134 --> 00:11:18,512
WHICH SUBJECT
IS MOST IMPORTANT?

314
00:11:18,595 --> 00:11:20,472
I WANT TO SHOW BRET
THAT I HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY.

315
00:11:20,556 --> 00:11:23,517
BOTH OF THESE ARE REALLY
"THINKY."

316
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,768
WHY NOT AIM FOR SOMETHING
MORE ACHIEVABLE?

317
00:11:24,852 --> 00:11:25,853
ELI:
NO. I NEED TO IMPRESS HIM

318
00:11:25,936 --> 00:11:27,354
IF I WANNA GET THIS
REFERENCE LETTER.

319
00:11:27,437 --> 00:11:29,273
OKAY. WHAT YOU DO NEED
IS TO RELAX.

320
00:11:29,356 --> 00:11:30,941
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

321
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:33,026
I'VE GOTTA RUN.
BUT YOU CAN DO THIS.

322
00:11:33,110 --> 00:11:34,611
MAYBE JAKE CAN HELP YOU?

323
00:11:35,654 --> 00:11:37,698
YOU STRUGGLING?

324
00:11:37,781 --> 00:11:40,367
MY MOVIE IS ALREADY
"IN THE CAN,"

325
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:42,369
AS THEY SAY.

326
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:43,829
YEAH. I'M SPINNING.

327
00:11:43,912 --> 00:11:45,664
NONE OF MY IDEAS
HAVE BEEN GOOD ENOUGH.

328
00:11:45,747 --> 00:11:48,250
I JUST FILMED A PLASTIC BAG
FLOATING IN THE WIND.

329
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,835
FOR TWO WHOLE MINUTES?

330
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:52,421
YEAH.
IT'S PROBABLY STILL THERE.

331
00:11:52,504 --> 00:11:54,339
HOW'D YOU COME UP
WITH THAT IDEA?

332
00:11:54,423 --> 00:11:55,632
PLEASE, JAKE,
I'M DESPERATE.

333
00:11:55,716 --> 00:11:58,552
(EXHALES)

334
00:11:58,635 --> 00:12:02,764
OKAY, BUT IT'S GOTTA STAY
OUR LITTLE SECRET.
YEAH.

335
00:12:11,648 --> 00:12:13,942
WHY SO GLUM?

336
00:12:14,026 --> 00:12:16,612
DID THINGS NOT GO WELL
WITH ADAM LAST NIGHT?

337
00:12:16,695 --> 00:12:18,655
I'M PRETTY SURE
HE LIKES ME.

338
00:12:18,739 --> 00:12:20,240
OH, BECKY,
THAT'S EXCITING.

339
00:12:21,742 --> 00:12:24,119
WHY AREN'T YOU
DOING TWIRLS?

340
00:12:24,203 --> 00:12:25,662
I WAS,
UNTIL LUKE POINTED OUT

341
00:12:25,746 --> 00:12:27,706
THAT MY PARENTS
WILL NEVER APPROVE.

342
00:12:27,789 --> 00:12:29,249
ARE YOU SURE?
THEY SEEM REALLY NICE.

343
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:30,918
THEY ARE,

344
00:12:31,001 --> 00:12:32,794
BUT THEY'RE EXTREMELY
CONSERVATIVE.

345
00:12:32,878 --> 00:12:34,546
THEN KEEP HIM A SECRET.

346
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:36,798
LIE TO MY PARENTS?

347
00:12:36,882 --> 00:12:38,509
DON'T LIE.
JUST DON'T TELL THEM.

348
00:12:41,512 --> 00:12:44,181
TOWNSEND:
DON QUIXOTE IMAGINES A WORLD
WHERE CHIVALRY IS NOT DEAD.

349
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:46,183
NOW THE AUTHOR MAKES THIS POINT

350
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:48,477
BY GIVING US
A BRILLIANT LITERARY CIPHER

351
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:50,979
IN THE FORM OF THE NOVEL'S
NEVER GLIMPSED DULCINEA.

352
00:12:53,774 --> 00:12:55,484
BECKY BAKER,

353
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:57,402
WHAT ARE YOUR THOUGHTS
ON THE ELUSIVE DULCINEA?

354
00:12:57,486 --> 00:12:59,363
ACTUALLY, SIR,

355
00:12:59,446 --> 00:13:01,031
I WAS HOPING
FOR A HALL PASS?

356
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:02,616
RIGHT, WELL,
MAKE IT QUICK!

357
00:13:04,535 --> 00:13:06,036
ANYONE ELSE?

358
00:13:16,088 --> 00:13:18,257
ADAM, I REALLY,
REALLY LIKE YOU.

359
00:13:23,470 --> 00:13:25,806
I'M SENSING A
"BUT YOU'RE TRANSGENDER."

360
00:13:28,392 --> 00:13:30,269
I SHOULD'VE KNOWN BETTER
THAN TO FALL FOR YOU.

361
00:13:30,352 --> 00:13:32,563
YOU FELL FOR ME?

362
00:13:32,646 --> 00:13:34,147
THE FIRST TIME
I MET YOU.

363
00:13:35,983 --> 00:13:37,484
ADAM,
I LIKE YOU A LOT.

364
00:13:39,444 --> 00:13:41,655
BUT MY PARENTS,
THEY'RE TRADITIONAL.

365
00:13:41,738 --> 00:13:44,533
THEY'LL NEVER APPROVE.

366
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:46,118
BUT YOU'RE OKAY WITH ME?

367
00:13:49,371 --> 00:13:51,498
WILL YOU BE
MY SECRET BOYFRIEND?

368
00:13:51,582 --> 00:13:53,625
I'M NOT ASHAMED,

369
00:13:53,709 --> 00:13:54,126
I JUST DON'T WANT THEM
TO FORBID ME FROM SEEING YOU.

370
00:13:54,209 --> 00:13:55,711
STOP.

371
00:13:55,794 --> 00:13:57,337
GO BACK TO THE PART

372
00:13:57,421 --> 00:13:59,339
WHERE YOU ASKED ME
TO BE YOUR BOYFRIEND.

373
00:13:59,965 --> 00:14:01,425
WILL YOU?

374
00:14:01,508 --> 00:14:03,010
SURE. WHY NOT?

375
00:14:22,905 --> 00:14:24,698
JAKE:
OKAY. YOU CAN'T TELL CLARE.

376
00:14:24,781 --> 00:14:26,950
ELI:
BUT WE SHARE EVERYTHING.

377
00:14:27,034 --> 00:14:29,536
JAKE:
PLEASE TELL ME YOU'RE KIDDING.
EVERYTHING?

378
00:14:29,620 --> 00:14:32,539
WELL, NOT EVERYTHING,
BUT... MOST THINGS.

379
00:14:32,623 --> 00:14:33,832
JAKE:
BUT YOU CAN'T TELL HER THIS.

380
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:34,625
YOU GOTTA-
YOU GOTTA PROMISE.

381
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:35,501
YEAH, YEAH,
I PROMISE.

382
00:14:35,584 --> 00:14:37,628
CROSS YOUR HEART?

383
00:14:37,711 --> 00:14:39,505
OKAY, WHY ARE YOU
ACTING SO WEIRD?

384
00:14:41,465 --> 00:14:43,967
THAT'S YOUR SECRET -
POT?

385
00:14:44,051 --> 00:14:45,552
WELL, I PREFER TO CALL IT
BY ITS PROPER NAME.

386
00:14:45,636 --> 00:14:48,055
MARIJUANA.

387
00:14:48,138 --> 00:14:50,224
YOU WERE ON DRUGS
WHEN YOU SHOT YOUR FILM?

388
00:14:50,307 --> 00:14:52,976
YEAH, YEAH.
MOST DEFINITELY, YEAH.

389
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:54,311
BUT IF YOU'RE NOT INTERESTED...

390
00:14:54,394 --> 00:14:55,896
I'M NO PUSHER.

391
00:14:57,564 --> 00:14:59,066
WAIT. HOL-

392
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:05,072
DO I HAVE
TO INHALE?

393
00:15:07,282 --> 00:15:09,284
I DON'T KNOW, B.

394
00:15:09,368 --> 00:15:09,952
YOU REALLY THINK THE DOT'S
A BIG ENOUGH PLACE

395
00:15:10,035 --> 00:15:11,537
FOR A WEDDING?

396
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:15,374
OH MY GOD, WE GOTTA GO.
MY MOM'S HERE.

397
00:15:15,457 --> 00:15:17,501
HEY, I LIED ABOUT
THE WEDDING STUFF.

398
00:15:17,584 --> 00:15:18,710
I ASKED AUDRA
TO MEET US HERE.

399
00:15:18,794 --> 00:15:20,128
YOU TRICKED ME?

400
00:15:20,212 --> 00:15:21,922
IT SUCKS TO BE LIED TO,
RIGHT?

401
00:15:22,005 --> 00:15:23,590
I CAN'T LIE TO AUDRA
ANYMORE, DREW.

402
00:15:23,674 --> 00:15:24,216
IF WE TELL HER,
SHE'LL FIND A WAY

403
00:15:24,299 --> 00:15:26,051
TO RUIN EVERYTHING!

404
00:15:26,134 --> 00:15:27,845
LOOK, AUDRA IS THE CLOSEST THING
I'VE EVER HAD TO A MOM,

405
00:15:27,928 --> 00:15:28,804
AND IT'S REALLY
IMPORTANT TO ME

406
00:15:28,887 --> 00:15:30,472
THAT SHE'S A PART
OF THIS.

407
00:15:30,556 --> 00:15:32,057
(SIGHS)

408
00:15:33,225 --> 00:15:34,852
SHE MEANS THAT MUCH
TO YOU?

409
00:15:37,354 --> 00:15:40,315
ALL RIGHT. FINE.
IF IT'LL MAKE YOU HAPPY.

410
00:15:40,399 --> 00:15:41,900
REALLY?
YEAH.

411
00:15:55,747 --> 00:15:57,749
MR. BAKER:
WHO'S A?

412
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,334
BECKY:
ADAM.

413
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,545
MR. BAKER:
IS THIS ADAM A BOYFRIEND?

414
00:16:03,589 --> 00:16:06,592
UM, HE'S A BOY
WHO'S A FRIEND.

415
00:16:06,675 --> 00:16:09,928
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE NOT
JUST LYING TO ME, BECKY.

416
00:16:10,012 --> 00:16:12,681
OKAY, ADAM'S A LITTLE MORE
THAN A FRIEND.

417
00:16:15,559 --> 00:16:17,686
SO WHEN DO I MEET HIM?

418
00:16:17,769 --> 00:16:19,188
WHAT?!

419
00:16:19,271 --> 00:16:21,106
YOU KNOW MY RULES,
KIDDO.

420
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:22,524
BE POLITE,
SAY MY PRAYERS,

421
00:16:22,608 --> 00:16:23,650
AND BRUSH AFTER
EVERY MEAL?

422
00:16:23,734 --> 00:16:25,777
ABOUT BOYS.

423
00:16:25,861 --> 00:16:26,737
YOU'RE ONLY ALLOWED
TO DATE IF...

424
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:29,239
YOU MEET THE GUY FIRST.

425
00:16:29,323 --> 00:16:31,450
WHY DON'T YOU ASK HIM OVER
FOR DINNER, TONIGHT?!

426
00:16:31,533 --> 00:16:33,160
UH, I THINK HE'S BUSY.

427
00:16:35,621 --> 00:16:36,914
IS THERE SOME REASON

428
00:16:36,997 --> 00:16:38,457
WHY YOU DON'T WANT US
TO MEET HIM?

429
00:16:38,540 --> 00:16:39,583
DOES HE HAVE A TATTOO?

430
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,877
NO. NO TATTOO.

431
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,712
HE DRIVES
A MOTORCYCLE?
DAD...

432
00:16:43,795 --> 00:16:44,713
WELL, THERE IS GOTTA BE
SOMETHING WRONG WITH HIM

433
00:16:44,796 --> 00:16:45,797
IF YOU HAVEN'T
BROUGHT HIM HOME.

434
00:16:45,881 --> 00:16:49,259
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH HIM.

435
00:16:49,343 --> 00:16:51,887
HE'S THE NICEST GUY
I'VE EVER MET.

436
00:16:51,970 --> 00:16:53,472
THEN IT'S SETTLED.
INVITE HIM OVER.

437
00:16:55,641 --> 00:16:57,142
OKAY.

438
00:16:59,978 --> 00:17:00,312
I PROMISE
I WON'T EMBARRASS YOU,

439
00:17:00,395 --> 00:17:02,397
BUTTERCUP.

440
00:17:02,481 --> 00:17:04,149
ALTHOUGH I CAN'T SPEAK
FOR YOUR MOTHER.

441
00:17:06,318 --> 00:17:09,404
AUDRA:
MY SON, IN THE FLESH.

442
00:17:09,488 --> 00:17:10,739
YOU KNOW, WHEN BIANCA TOLD ME
YOU WANTED TO TALK,

443
00:17:10,822 --> 00:17:12,783
I'LL BE HONEST,
I DIDN'T BELIEVE IT.

444
00:17:15,244 --> 00:17:18,038
DREW CAME BECAUSE
WE HAVE SOMETHING TO TELL YOU.

445
00:17:18,121 --> 00:17:19,498
OH GOD,
YOU'RE PREGNANT!

446
00:17:19,581 --> 00:17:22,209
NO! NO. GOD, NO.

447
00:17:22,292 --> 00:17:24,503
(RELIEVED SIGH)
THANK GOODNESS.

448
00:17:24,586 --> 00:17:27,089
OH, I'M TOO YOUNG
TO BE A GRANDMOTHER.

449
00:17:33,428 --> 00:17:35,013
WE'RE GETTING MARRIED
THIS SUMMER.

450
00:17:37,558 --> 00:17:39,142
SERIOUSLY?
YOU CAN'T STOP US.

451
00:17:39,226 --> 00:17:40,727
DREW,
LET YOUR MOM SPEAK.

452
00:17:42,938 --> 00:17:44,565
YOU DON'T HAVE
LIFE EXPERIENCE

453
00:17:44,648 --> 00:17:47,025
TO MAKE THIS DECISION.

454
00:17:47,109 --> 00:17:48,777
YOU DIDN'T EVEN GRADUATE
FROM HIGH SCHOOL.

455
00:17:48,861 --> 00:17:50,821
THANKS FOR BEING
SO PREDICTABLE, MOM.

456
00:17:50,904 --> 00:17:52,030
BIANCA:
WE WILL BY THE TIME
WE GET MARRIED,

457
00:17:52,114 --> 00:17:53,699
AND DREW PROMISED ME
HE'D GET HIS GED.

458
00:17:53,782 --> 00:17:55,617
WHATEVER.
I'M OUTTA HERE.

459
00:17:55,701 --> 00:17:57,202
AUDRA:
DREW!

460
00:17:58,912 --> 00:18:00,414
BIANCA.
BIANCA...

461
00:18:01,665 --> 00:18:04,001
YOU HAVE COME SO FAR.

462
00:18:04,084 --> 00:18:05,002
WHY NOT JUST WAIT
UNTIL YOU'VE GRADUATED

463
00:18:05,085 --> 00:18:06,128
FROM UNIVERSITY?

464
00:18:06,211 --> 00:18:07,713
WHY RUSH THIS?

465
00:18:09,756 --> 00:18:12,593
(DREW KNOCKS ON GLASS)
YOU COMING OR WHAT?

466
00:18:12,676 --> 00:18:14,511
BIANCA, PLEASE,
THINK ABOUT IT.

467
00:18:17,931 --> 00:18:19,433
I'M SORRY.

468
00:18:33,447 --> 00:18:34,948
(PHONE RINGS)

469
00:18:36,909 --> 00:18:38,035
ADAM:
HELLO?

470
00:18:38,118 --> 00:18:39,995
ARE YOU FREE TONIGHT?

471
00:18:40,078 --> 00:18:41,580
ADAM:
UH... I COULD BE.
MOVIE?

472
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:45,250
NO. MY PARENTS KINDA WANNA
HAVE YOU OVER.

473
00:18:47,503 --> 00:18:48,921
BUT IF YOU'RE BUSY
IT'S TOTALLY OKAY.

474
00:18:49,004 --> 00:18:50,506
I CAN RESCHEDULE.

475
00:18:50,589 --> 00:18:52,966
HOW DO YOUR PARENTS KNOW
I EXIST?

476
00:18:53,050 --> 00:18:55,344
BECKY:
UM, MY DAD'S JUST SUCH
A GOOD GUESSER.

477
00:18:55,427 --> 00:18:57,262
I MEAN, YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT A GOOD GUESSER MY DAD IS.

478
00:18:57,346 --> 00:18:58,722
YOU'RE A TERRIBLE LIAR.

479
00:18:58,805 --> 00:19:01,099
OKAY.

480
00:19:01,183 --> 00:19:03,018
I ACCIDENTALLY TOLD HIM
I HAVE A BOYFRIEND,

481
00:19:03,101 --> 00:19:04,645
AND NOW HE WANTS
TO MEET YOU.

482
00:19:04,728 --> 00:19:06,563
SOMEONE CAN'T KEEP A SECRET.

483
00:19:06,647 --> 00:19:08,357
WHAT'RE WE GONNA DO?

484
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:10,192
UH, EAT DINNER?
MAYBE DESSERT.

485
00:19:10,275 --> 00:19:11,985
ADAM, THIS IS SERIOUS.

486
00:19:12,069 --> 00:19:13,904
OKAY. I'M SORRY.
UM...

487
00:19:13,987 --> 00:19:15,280
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.

488
00:19:15,364 --> 00:19:17,783
NO! IT'S NOT GONNA BE OKAY.

489
00:19:17,866 --> 00:19:19,493
IF MY PARENTS MEET YOU,
THEY'LL FREAK OUT.

490
00:19:19,576 --> 00:19:21,078
THEY'LL NEVER LET US
SEE EACH OTHER.

491
00:19:21,161 --> 00:19:22,663
WE NEED A PLAN.

492
00:19:22,746 --> 00:19:24,373
BECKY, I'M A BOY.

493
00:19:26,375 --> 00:19:29,419
I KNOW THAT,
BUT MY DAD-

494
00:19:29,503 --> 00:19:31,463
I PASSED WHEN I MET YOU,
RIGHT?

495
00:19:31,547 --> 00:19:33,590
THAT'S TRUE.

496
00:19:33,674 --> 00:19:35,175
UNLESS THEY ASK TO SEE
MY DRIVERS' LICENSE,

497
00:19:35,259 --> 00:19:36,593
YOUR PARENTS
WILL HAVE NO CLUE.

498
00:19:36,677 --> 00:19:38,178
I PROMISE.

499
00:19:39,721 --> 00:19:41,348
ARE YOU SURE
WE CAN DO THIS?

500
00:19:41,431 --> 00:19:42,933
ADAM:
TRUST ME.

501
00:19:46,854 --> 00:19:48,897
ELI:
I-I CAN'T BELIEVE
HOW OBVIOUS THIS WAS!

502
00:19:51,859 --> 00:19:53,443
HEY, YOU JUST NEEDED
A LITTLE NUDGE.

503
00:19:53,527 --> 00:19:55,529
IT'S ABOUT LOVE, LIFE,
WAR, LOVE...

504
00:19:57,281 --> 00:19:58,323
I SAID LOVE TWICE.

505
00:19:58,407 --> 00:19:59,783
BUT THAT'S OKAY

506
00:19:59,867 --> 00:20:01,743
BECAUSE LOVE IS
A BIG PART OF LIFE.

507
00:20:01,827 --> 00:20:03,537
OH, THAT IS GOOD.

508
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:05,289
I NEED REMEMBER THAT
SO I CAN SAY THAT TO BRET.

509
00:20:05,372 --> 00:20:06,415
UH, PEN ME.

510
00:20:06,498 --> 00:20:08,000
JAKE:
YEAH!

511
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:10,377
(PEN CLATTERS ON FLOOR)

512
00:20:10,460 --> 00:20:11,837
YOU KNOW WHAT? FORGET IT.
I'LL REMEMBER IT.

513
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:13,547
WAIT. WHAT'D I SAY?

514
00:20:13,630 --> 00:20:15,424
SOMETHING ABOUT LIFE.

515
00:20:15,507 --> 00:20:16,675
OKAY! UM...

516
00:20:16,758 --> 00:20:19,845
NEW TITLE: "LIFE."

517
00:20:19,928 --> 00:20:24,016
NO! NO! NO!
"LIFE: THE SHORT FILM."

518
00:20:24,099 --> 00:20:26,518
(TALKING TO HIMSELF)
AND WE CROSS-FADE...
UH, WIPE TO COLOUR,

519
00:20:26,602 --> 00:20:27,811
THEN BACK TO BLACK AND WHITE.

520
00:20:27,895 --> 00:20:29,313
THEN WE FADE IN,

521
00:20:29,396 --> 00:20:33,358
AND UM... STAR WIPE,

522
00:20:33,442 --> 00:20:35,194
FADE BACK OUT.

523
00:20:35,277 --> 00:20:36,778
AND...THE END.

524
00:20:39,281 --> 00:20:41,408
THIS IS THE BEST THING
I'VE EVER DONE.

525
00:20:41,491 --> 00:20:42,993
JAKE:
DO YOU HEAR A RINGING?

526
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:46,079
MR. BAKER:
SO, ADAM,

527
00:20:46,163 --> 00:20:46,997
WHY DON'T YOU TELL US
A BIT ABOUT YOUR FAMILY.

528
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,874
WELL-

529
00:20:48,957 --> 00:20:50,417
HIS MOM'S ON THE PTA.
HIS DAD'S A LAWYER.

530
00:20:50,501 --> 00:20:52,419
HE HAS AN OLDER BROTHER.

531
00:20:52,503 --> 00:20:55,297
HIS FAMILY IS NORMAL.
TOTALLY, TOTALLY NORMAL.

532
00:20:55,380 --> 00:20:57,674
ADAM:
THAT'S THE LIGHTNING ROUND
VERSION.

533
00:20:57,758 --> 00:20:58,926
MRS. BAKER:
SO BECKY TELLS US
YOUR FAMILY IS CHRISTIAN?

534
00:20:59,009 --> 00:21:00,594
BECKY:
CATHOLIC.

535
00:21:00,677 --> 00:21:02,137
THEY GO TO ST. MARY'S CHURCH
EVERY SUNDAY.

536
00:21:02,221 --> 00:21:03,680
MR. BAKER:
BECKY, LET THE BOY SPEAK!

537
00:21:03,764 --> 00:21:05,307
NO. IT'S OKAY.

538
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:08,519
UH, MY TURN.
WHAT'S MY FAVOURITE MOVIE?

539
00:21:08,602 --> 00:21:09,978
BECKY:
I DON'T KNOW.

540
00:21:10,062 --> 00:21:12,856
MR. BAKER:
AH, YOU STUMPED HER!
UP TOP.

541
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:14,358
SO, ADAM,
YOU PLAY ANY SPORTS?

542
00:21:14,441 --> 00:21:15,817
I WAS ALWAYS TOO SMALL
AS A KID.

543
00:21:15,901 --> 00:21:16,527
BUT I'M ACTUALLY THINKING
OF GOING OUT

544
00:21:16,610 --> 00:21:17,528
FOR SOMETHING THIS YEAR.

545
00:21:17,611 --> 00:21:18,570
A GUYS' TEAM?

546
00:21:18,654 --> 00:21:20,030
BECKY:
LUKE!

547
00:21:20,113 --> 00:21:22,533
NO, I UNDERSTAND
HIS CONFUSION.

548
00:21:22,616 --> 00:21:24,117
THEY ONLY LET YOU PLAY
ON GIRLS' HOCKEY, RIGHT?

549
00:21:24,201 --> 00:21:25,702
(BECKY GIGGLES)

550
00:21:27,621 --> 00:21:29,748
LUKE:
I'D LIKE TO MAKE A TOAST.

551
00:21:29,831 --> 00:21:31,750
TO BECKY'S BOYFRIEND.

552
00:21:31,834 --> 00:21:35,420
HE'S A BRAVE GUY
FOR DATING MY SISTER.

553
00:21:35,504 --> 00:21:36,672
MR. BAKER: TO ADAM!
MRS. BAKER: ADAM!

554
00:21:36,755 --> 00:21:38,841
(GLASSES CLINK)

555
00:21:38,924 --> 00:21:42,010
♪ Your love is
like a tidal wave ♪

556
00:21:42,094 --> 00:21:44,137
♪ Let me dive in ♪

557
00:21:44,221 --> 00:21:46,181
♪ Let me feel your grey ♪

558
00:21:46,265 --> 00:21:48,392
♪ Yes, your love will
wash me away ♪

